      "rationale": "FE-predicted principal surface strains compared against rosette strain gauge measurements at 12 locations across three cadaveric specimens. Mean absolute relative error 6.8%; all predictions within ±15% band. Pearson correlation r = 0.97; slope of regression line 0.98 (95% CI: 0.94–1.02). Statistical equivalence test (TOST) confirms predictions are within pre-specified acceptance threshold of ±15%."
